This paper deals with the self-organization of nodes in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and network science (DS). The use of bio-inspired algorithms and simple interactions between neighboring nodes suggests a focus on machine learning (MA) and artificial intelligence (SI). Additionally, the use of beamforming techniques suggests a possible connection to information theory (IT).
